    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offering a driver-spec 2011 BMW M3 featuring the high-revving S65 4.0L V8. This naturally aspirated powerplant utilizes eight individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing to produce a linear power band peaking at an 8,400 RPM redline. The drivetrain consists of a tactile 6-speed manual transmission paired with a Variable M Differential Lock for optimal torque distribution. The chassis is supported by Electronic Damper Control (EDC), providing three-stage adjustable damping to manage lateral load transfer effectively. This example has undergone critical preventative maintenance, including rod bearing replacement with treated shells and upgraded throttle valve actuators, addressing the primary concerns of the S65 architecture. The subframe and bushings remain in solid condition, ensuring the precise handling characteristics expected of the E92 platform. A mechanically sound, performance-oriented machine for the serious enthusiast.",
      "price": 34800.0,
